## Color

Tokens are **CSS custom properties** declared in `:root` in `styles/_variables.scss`
(light/default) and overridden per theme in `styles/_themes.scss`. Reference them
in component SCSS as `var(--color-*)`. Document intent here; the SCSS holds values.

| Token | Role | _(todo: value)_ |
|---|---|---|
| `--color-bg` | page background | |
| `--color-surface` / `--color-surface-2` | raised surfaces | |
| `--color-primary` / `--color-primary-fg` | single accent + its foreground | |
| `--color-text` / `--color-text-muted` | text ramp | |
| `--color-border` | hairline borders | |

Rule: **one accent.** Semantic colors (`--color-danger` / `--color-success`) only when something is genuinely that state.

## Typography

Fonts are CSS custom properties (`--font-body`, `--font-mono`, plus any you add
such as `--font-heading`) in `styles/_variables.scss`. For web fonts, add a single
`@import url(...)` (or `@font-face`) at the top of `_variables.scss`.

| Token | Used for | _(todo: stack)_ |
|---|---|---|
| `--font-heading` | display / headings (add if needed) | |
| `--font-body` | body copy | |
| `--font-mono` | labels / numeric / code | |

Rule: components use `font-family: var(--font-*)` — **never** a raw `font-family` string.

## Spacing & radii

Use the `--space-*` and `--radius-*` scales (CSS custom properties in
`_variables.scss`). Breakpoints are Sass `$bp-*` vars in `_variables.scss`, used by
the responsive mixins. Don't introduce ad-hoc pixel values; extend the scale instead.

## Component design

- Prefer small, single-purpose components; break sections into discrete, reusable pieces.
- One `Component.scss` per component, imported once at the top of the component, with real class names (no CSS modules).
- Mobile-first: base styles target small screens; layer up with the `@include tablet` / `@include desktop` mixins from `styles/_responsive.scss`. Wrap animations in `@include respect-reduced-motion`.
- Reuse before creating — consult [`COMPONENT_INDEX.md`](./COMPONENT_INDEX.md) first.

